                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d391">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Ryan</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Blaine</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1890-07-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 30, 1890</date>. (Received July
                        31.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Ryan reports that the Guatemalan minister to Mexico has always assured him
                    that the Guatemalan Government in no way interferes with either official or
                    other correspondence. Dispatches thence are regularly, and, as he claims,
                    without censorship, received by the agent of the American Associated Press,
                    though the Mexican minister for foreign affairs is unable to receive anything
                    from the Mexican minister to Guatemala. The minister for Guatemala to Mexico has
                    telegraphed, at Mr. Ryan’s request, to the Guatemalan minister for foreign
                    affairs for positive information, and inviolability will be demanded if no
                    satisfactory reply is received.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
